WEBVTT

00:00.367 --> 00:04.103
Show me "wax on, wax off."

00:04.105 --> 00:05.037
Hyah!

00:05.039 --> 00:09.441
<i>(CENTERFOLD</i> PLAYING)

00:12.612 --> 00:13.912
ADAM:  <i>Man, I love the '80s.</i>

00:13.914 --> 00:17.383
<i>It was the age of</i> E.T.,
<i>Mr. T., and MTV.</i>

00:17.385 --> 00:18.884
<i>Back then,</i>
<i>the world was still small...</i>

00:18.886 --> 00:21.520
<i>No cell phones</i>
<i>or internet or Twitter.</i>

00:21.522 --> 00:22.755
<i>Your friends lived</i>
<i>on your street,</i>

00:22.757 --> 00:26.125
<i>and your family</i>
<i>were the people</i>
<i>at your dinner table.</i>

00:26.127 --> 00:26.959
(RECORD NEEDLE SCRATCHES)

00:26.961 --> 00:30.262
<i>If you're assuming these</i>
<i>smiley, affectionate people</i>
<i>are my family, they're not.</i>

00:30.264 --> 00:32.498
<i>We showed our affection</i>
<i>in a different way.</i>

00:32.500 --> 00:33.732
Yeah, does this hurt?
No, it doesn't hurt.

00:33.734 --> 00:36.802
Erica, not at the table.
It doesn't hurt.
It doesn't hurt.

00:36.804 --> 00:38.704
MAN:  <i>Now this is how</i>
<i>I remember the '80s.</i>

00:38.706 --> 00:42.341
<i>There were no parenting blogs</i>
<i>or peanut allergies...</i>

00:42.343 --> 00:44.109
<i>Just a whole lot of crazy.</i>

00:44.111 --> 00:45.744
<i>Oh, look at</i>
<i>that little geek, right?</i>

00:45.746 --> 00:47.713
<i>Yeah, that's me,</i>
<i>Adam Goldberg.</i>

00:47.715 --> 00:50.349
<i>We were the first on our block</i>
<i>to get a video camera,</i>

00:50.351 --> 00:53.952
<i>and I used it to record</i>
<i>my entire childhood.</i>

00:53.954 --> 00:54.686
(SINGSONGY)  <i>I'm home!</i>

00:54.688 --> 00:56.522
<i>The man parking his pants</i>
<i>at the front door...</i>

00:56.524 --> 00:59.224
<i>That's my dad,</i>
<i>Murray Goldberg.</i>

00:59.226 --> 01:00.459
<i>TV's mine!</i>

01:00.461 --> 01:01.460
<i>Ever since</i>
<i>his last heart attack,</i>

01:01.462 --> 01:04.530
<i>he became determined</i>
<i>to exercise, eat better,</i>

01:04.532 --> 01:07.099
<i>and not yell so much.</i>
<i>It wasn't working.</i>

01:07.101 --> 01:08.133
<i>Stop with the camera!</i>

01:08.135 --> 01:10.202
<i>My super friendly sister</i>
<i>Erica...</i>

01:10.204 --> 01:12.604
<i>She loved to talk to people,</i>
<i>just not us.</i>

01:12.606 --> 01:15.707
<i>Adam, what the hell?</i>
<i>I'm gonna crimp your face!</i>

01:15.709 --> 01:16.208
<i>Mom!</i>

01:16.210 --> 01:21.447
<i>Barry Goldberg,</i>
<i>textbook middle child</i>
<i>and classic overreactor.</i>

01:21.449 --> 01:23.415
<i>You're a liar, Simon!</i>

01:23.417 --> 01:24.750
<i>You are a liar!</i>

01:24.752 --> 01:26.351
(BUZZING)

01:26.353 --> 01:27.319
<i>Stop videotaping!</i>

01:27.321 --> 01:31.356
<i>And finally,</i>
<i>my overbearing smother,</i>
<i>Beverly Goldberg,</i>

01:31.358 --> 01:33.859
<i>a homemaker,</i>
<i>a ball breaker,</i>

01:33.861 --> 01:35.094
<i>who found the time</i>
<i>to stay fit,</i>

01:35.096 --> 01:38.564
<i>raise the kids,</i>
<i>and drive us all insane.</i>

01:38.566 --> 01:39.264
(ALL SHOUTING AT ONCE)

01:39.266 --> 01:41.033
<i>Yeah, we were the family</i>
<i>that yelled and cursed,</i>

01:41.035 --> 01:45.370
<i>but to this day,</i>
<i>we still love each other.</i>

01:45.605 --> 01:47.406
<i>This is my family...</i>

01:47.408 --> 01:50.008
(READING)

01:50.243 --> 01:51.176
<i>It was September 3rd.</i>

01:51.178 --> 01:53.679
<i>It began as a typical morning</i>
<i>in the Goldberg house.</i>

01:53.681 --> 01:57.483
You don't know anything.
He's not too old for me.

01:57.485 --> 01:59.017
He's in college, Erica!

01:59.019 --> 02:01.353
Wrong! He dropped out
to start a band.

02:01.355 --> 02:02.688
Don't you feel
stupid now?

02:02.690 --> 02:06.191
Mom, they don't zip!
Can you help me with this?

02:06.193 --> 02:07.860
Oh! Look at you!

02:07.862 --> 02:11.997
Oh, why go shopping
when your sister's jeans
fit you so perfectly?

02:11.999 --> 02:13.465
Fit me perfectly?
They're horrible!

02:13.467 --> 02:16.068
They're roomy in the hips
and tight in the front.

02:16.070 --> 02:17.870
I look like
Brooke Shields.

02:17.872 --> 02:18.670
And she's beautiful.

02:18.672 --> 02:23.175
Look, you need to be grateful,
because one day I won't be
here to help dress you.

02:23.177 --> 02:25.344
You keep saying that,
but when? God.

02:25.346 --> 02:28.113
ADAM:  <i>As always, my mom began</i>
<i>the day by dressing us,</i>

02:28.115 --> 02:31.650
<i>feeding us, and ignoring</i>
<i>any sense of human boundaries.</i>

02:31.652 --> 02:32.818
(SINGSONGY)
Where's my baby?

02:32.820 --> 02:34.520
(GASPS)
(CURTAIN RINGS SWOOSH)

02:34.522 --> 02:35.554
Happy birthday!

02:35.556 --> 02:38.490
(NORMAL VOICE) What do you
want for breakfast?
Privacy!

02:38.492 --> 02:40.392
Oh, please.

02:40.394 --> 02:42.027
Don't forget to wash
your bottom.

02:42.029 --> 02:44.096
ADAM:  <i>Barry was in</i>
<i>a rare good mood.</i>

02:44.098 --> 02:44.997
<i>He was turning 16,</i>

02:44.999 --> 02:48.033
<i>a day he'd been</i>
<i>waiting for his whole life.</i>

02:48.035 --> 02:49.768
(RATTLES)
It's jingling.

02:49.770 --> 02:51.837
It's keys!
Keys means car!

02:51.839 --> 02:53.906
Car means freedom
from all you monsters!

02:53.908 --> 02:55.140
I love you, mom.

02:55.142 --> 02:56.742
(WRAPPING PAPER RUSTLES)

02:56.744 --> 02:58.377
(BOX LID CLATTERS)

02:58.545 --> 03:00.078
What the hell is this?

03:00.080 --> 03:00.913
It's a locket.

03:00.915 --> 03:07.486
It's got my picture inside
so you can always have
your mother near your heart.

03:08.254 --> 03:10.189
Sweetie, you're just
not ready to drive.

03:10.191 --> 03:14.326
You're too immature,
and quite honestly,
a little high strung.

03:14.328 --> 03:15.360
I am not high strung!

03:15.362 --> 03:17.696
I'm strung just fine,
like a tennis racket
or a banjo. I...

03:17.698 --> 03:21.900
You know, I think it's great,
'cause all the cool guys
in my grade,

03:21.902 --> 03:23.101
they have
mom lockets.

03:23.103 --> 03:24.136
Hey!
All of 'em.
(SNICKERS)

03:24.138 --> 03:25.804
Don't poke the bear,
all right?

03:25.806 --> 03:28.507
You don't wanna wear it?
Fine.

03:28.509 --> 03:29.808
I'll throw it
in the trash.

03:29.810 --> 03:31.376
Go ahead. Do it.
Here I go.

03:31.378 --> 03:32.544
Going to the trash.
Do it. Go ahead.

03:32.546 --> 03:34.780
Gonna go in
the garbage.
Mm-hmm.

03:34.782 --> 03:36.114
(CHAIN JANGLES)

03:36.116 --> 03:37.382
Unbelievable!

03:37.384 --> 03:39.751
You were gonna let me
throw this in the trash?

03:39.753 --> 03:41.220
Totally irresponsible.
You're not driving.

03:41.222 --> 03:43.655
Oh, god. Dad, please talk
some sense into your wife.

03:43.657 --> 03:46.191
She's saying some
pretty controversial
things over there.

03:46.193 --> 03:49.494
I agree with
whatever nonsense
your mother just said.

03:49.496 --> 03:52.130
Come on.
This is not fair!

03:52.132 --> 03:54.967
Who the hell told you
life was fair, you moron?

03:54.969 --> 03:57.603
ADAM:  <i>Dad's colorful</i>
<i>way of speaking</i>
<i>may seem a bit harsh.</i>

03:57.605 --> 04:00.906
<i>It really wasn't.</i>
<i>You just had to learn</i>
<i>how to speak "Murray."</i>

04:00.908 --> 04:05.077
It's 2:00 a.m.
I thought you were dead!

04:05.079 --> 04:06.678
I could kill you!

04:06.680 --> 04:08.680
(BELL DINGS)

04:08.682 --> 04:09.214
(CLICK)

04:09.216 --> 04:11.750
You broke it?
It's amazing.

04:11.752 --> 04:14.553
You little bastards
ruin everything.

04:14.555 --> 04:16.622
(BELL DINGS)

04:18.191 --> 04:22.361
For someone so smart,
you sure act like an idiot.

04:22.363 --> 04:24.296
(BELL DINGS)

04:25.198 --> 04:28.166
All right,
stop your pouting.

04:28.168 --> 04:29.067
I got you something,

04:29.069 --> 04:31.670
and I think
you're gonna like it.

04:32.205 --> 04:34.840
(WRAPPING PAPER RUSTLES)

04:36.843 --> 04:39.978
REO Speedwagon?
This is top 40!

04:39.980 --> 04:44.383
You don't know me at all!
I'm into rap,
the poetry of the streets!

04:44.385 --> 04:45.584
Come on!
No, no, no.

04:45.586 --> 04:47.486
I talked to the guy
at Sam Goody.

04:47.488 --> 04:48.253
He said it was
a hip track.

04:48.255 --> 04:51.256
Well, did you talk
to Sam Goody himself? Huh?

04:51.258 --> 04:53.859
Did you? No. you talked
to a random jagoff

04:53.861 --> 04:55.260
who knows nothing
about real music.

04:55.262 --> 04:58.163
You weren't there, okay?
The guy had an earring.

04:58.165 --> 05:01.466
He had a jean jacket
covered in buttons! Covered!

05:01.468 --> 05:03.902
(CHAIR SCRAPES FLOOR)
Don't get your father
all worked up.

05:03.904 --> 05:05.437
I'm already
all worked up.
Honey.

05:05.439 --> 05:07.272
Breathe.
Calm down. Breathe,
breathe. I'm breathing.

05:07.274 --> 05:08.974
I'm breathing, okay?
You're killing your father.

05:08.976 --> 05:11.576
I hope you're having
a happy birthday.
(EXHALES)

05:11.578 --> 05:12.044
(HORN HONKS)

05:12.046 --> 05:13.578
BEREVRLY: Remember what
Dr. Hong said.
I know what Hong said!

05:13.580 --> 05:16.915
ADAM:  <i>Barry had</i>
<i>one last visitor,</i>
<i>my grandfather, Pops.</i>

05:16.917 --> 05:18.517
<i>He was 80 years</i>
<i>of pure awesome.</i>

05:18.519 --> 05:22.788
I hear someone turned 16
and could use a new car.

05:22.790 --> 05:24.222
Holy crap! For me?

05:24.224 --> 05:25.957
I don't love you
that much.

05:25.959 --> 05:28.460
This baby's mine.
You get my old one.

05:28.462 --> 05:31.797
Yes!
No! I didn't get a car
when I turned 16.

05:31.799 --> 05:32.964
What do you need
a car for?

05:32.966 --> 05:37.436
With your looks, you can get
a ride from any boy in town.

05:37.438 --> 05:39.037
Here you go.

05:39.039 --> 05:39.805
(DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYS)

05:39.807 --> 05:43.008
ADAM:  <i>It was the moment</i>
<i>Barry had waited for</i>
<i>his whole life.</i>

05:43.010 --> 05:47.813
<i>Those keys meant freedom,</i>
<i>and no man could stop him.</i>

05:47.815 --> 05:50.182
(MUSIC WARPS TO A STOP)

05:50.184 --> 05:51.049
<i>But my mom could.</i>

05:51.051 --> 05:53.985
Not gonna happen, dad.
We've decided
Barry can't drive.

05:53.987 --> 05:57.155
BARRY: What?
So Barry has a car
and no license,

05:57.157 --> 05:59.758
and I have a license
and no car.

05:59.760 --> 06:00.592
That makes no sense.

06:00.594 --> 06:02.027
You know what else
makes no sense?

06:02.029 --> 06:05.030
Those peach wine coolers
I found hiding in your closet.

06:05.032 --> 06:07.265
Yeah.
I'm everywhere.

06:07.267 --> 06:09.568
This is the worst
birthday ever!

06:09.570 --> 06:13.305
The only one who
understands me
is Flavor Flav.

06:16.843 --> 06:17.442
Who runs like that?

06:17.444 --> 06:20.645
And what, we having
a drag race?
What's with the bird car?

06:20.647 --> 06:22.981
Oh, my father thinks
he's Burt Reynolds.

06:22.983 --> 06:26.084
The sexiest man alive?
Yes, I do.

06:26.086 --> 06:28.987
Hey, kiddo, pick you up
after school?

06:28.989 --> 06:31.690
Um, we're going to the Y
to do some water aerobics.

06:31.692 --> 06:34.226
It's good for
his circulation.

06:34.228 --> 06:35.994
ADAM:
<i>Swimming was just our cover.</i>

06:35.996 --> 06:37.662
<i>Pops really took me</i>
<i>to the House of Waffles</i>

06:37.664 --> 06:39.564
<i>to teach me</i>
<i>the finer things in life.</i>

06:39.566 --> 06:42.534
And you can't just go in
and honk 'em.

06:42.536 --> 06:44.503
It's all about
the cuppage.

06:44.505 --> 06:47.606
Be gentle.
Those puppies are sensitive.

06:47.608 --> 06:50.275
I just wanna
bury my face in 'em.

06:50.277 --> 06:53.378
We all do,
but you gotta earn it.

06:53.713 --> 06:54.813
Speaking of,

06:54.815 --> 06:58.683
where are we
on Operation Waffle Girl?

07:02.755 --> 07:05.757
ADAM:  <i>Her name was</i>
<i>Zoe Macintosh.</i>

07:05.759 --> 07:07.492
<i>She was</i>
<i>the complete package.</i>

07:07.494 --> 07:13.031
<i>Beautiful, older, and her dad</i>
<i>was our family podiatrist.</i>

07:13.033 --> 07:13.765
Okay.

07:13.767 --> 07:15.700
Last week,
we told her your name.

07:15.702 --> 07:17.068
Let's see if it stuck.

07:17.070 --> 07:19.404
Oh, Miss?
Could you top me off?

07:19.406 --> 07:22.174
(LOWERED VOICE) No, no, Pops,
too ballsy. Pops, stop.

07:22.176 --> 07:25.577
No, no, we can't do this.
I'm not ready!

07:26.179 --> 07:27.979
(DEEP VOICE)
'Sup, girl?

07:28.815 --> 07:31.216
(NORMAL VOICE)
The check, please.

07:31.218 --> 07:32.818
You got it, Alan.

07:32.820 --> 07:35.287
Did you hear that?
She just called me "Alan"!

07:35.289 --> 07:36.054
That's not your name.

07:36.056 --> 07:39.257
I'll change it.
I'm Alan now.
Pops, you're a genius.

07:39.259 --> 07:41.359
Thank you, Jedi Master.

07:41.361 --> 07:43.628
(IMITATING
LIGHTSABER WHOOSHING)

07:45.998 --> 07:48.934
You're not making
this easy, kid.

07:48.936 --> 07:50.068
Sorry.

07:50.070 --> 07:50.535
(WHOOSHING)

07:50.537 --> 07:51.803
You're like my own personal
Obi-Wan Kenobi,

07:51.805 --> 07:56.174
but instead of the force,
you're teaching me
how to get freaky.

07:56.176 --> 07:57.909
Who's Oboe Cannoli?

07:57.911 --> 07:59.211
Is that Barry?

07:59.213 --> 08:01.213
Barry, what are you doing?

08:01.215 --> 08:02.247
Eating day-old doughnuts.

08:02.249 --> 08:04.816
My friend Terrance,
he's the manager.

08:04.818 --> 08:06.751
He leaves 'em
out back for me.

08:06.753 --> 08:07.219
Why?

08:07.221 --> 08:09.888
It's called eating
your feelings, assbag!

08:09.890 --> 08:12.491
Mom's gonna walk me
to the bus till I'm 40,
all right?

08:12.493 --> 08:13.692
Put down
the garbage cruller.

08:13.694 --> 08:18.964
I'm gonna figure out a way
to get you that license
and my car.

08:18.966 --> 08:21.099
Come on.
Really?

08:21.901 --> 08:25.804
ADAM:  <i>As we cruised</i>
<i>in Pops' new ride,</i>
<i>we felt like kings.</i>

08:25.806 --> 08:29.007
<i>It didn't matter that my mom</i>
<i>said Barry couldn't drive.</i>

08:29.009 --> 08:30.008
<i>Our grandfather</i>
<i>would fix that.</i>

08:30.010 --> 08:33.311
<i>He was always</i>
<i>cooking up a plan in</i>
<i>that brilliant mind of his.</i>

08:33.313 --> 08:37.816
All right, Pops,
you said you had a plan.
Whatchu thinkin'?

08:37.818 --> 08:39.818
Uh... Uh...

08:39.820 --> 08:41.553
Pops, you okay?

08:41.555 --> 08:44.256
(TIRES SCREECH)

08:44.657 --> 08:45.924
Aah!

08:45.926 --> 08:48.126
(LOUD CLATTER)

08:51.364 --> 08:52.497
(COUGHS)

08:52.499 --> 08:54.099
(ENGINE HISSING)

08:54.101 --> 08:56.368
ADAM:  <i>Okay, his mind</i>
<i>wasn't what it used to be,</i>

08:56.370 --> 08:58.837
<i>but his appetite still was.</i>

08:58.839 --> 09:00.805
So who wants nuggets?

09:03.543 --> 09:06.077
ADAM:  <i>Pops was booked</i>
<i>with reckless endangerment,</i>

09:06.079 --> 09:08.580
<i>and we were all thrown</i>
<i>behind bars...</i>

09:08.582 --> 09:10.682
<i>That is until</i>
<i>our mom arrived.</i>

09:10.684 --> 09:11.883
Are you proud of yourself?

09:11.885 --> 09:13.685
Locking up an old man
and two little boys?

09:13.687 --> 09:17.556
ADAM:  <i>God help the poor soul</i>
<i>who tried to push us around.</i>

09:17.558 --> 09:18.323
<i>That... Was her job.</i>

09:18.325 --> 09:22.027
Memorize this face,
because it is gonna haunt
your dreams, sir.

09:22.029 --> 09:26.932
It is gonna haunt
your (BLEEP) dreams!

09:27.433 --> 09:28.133
Are you guys okay?

09:28.135 --> 09:31.836
No, I'm not okay!
Barry took a dump
in front of us!

09:31.838 --> 09:33.405
I had to go!

09:34.774 --> 09:36.641
It was bad.

09:40.613 --> 09:42.213
I'm telling you,
it wasn't my fault.

09:42.215 --> 09:47.185
ADAM:  <i>The next morning,</i>
<i>mom lowered the boom</i>
<i>and took Pops' keys.</i>

09:47.187 --> 09:48.486
I'm not one
of your kids, Bev.

09:48.488 --> 09:51.923
You can't boss me around.
I do the bossing!

09:51.925 --> 09:53.858
Dad, I'm just trying
to help you.

09:53.860 --> 09:55.360
Your mind is not
what it used to be.

09:55.362 --> 09:57.195
ADAM:  <i>As always, the neighbors</i>
<i>came out to watch.</i>

09:57.197 --> 10:01.800
Oh, hello, Gina!
Why don't you take a picture?
It'll last longer!

10:01.802 --> 10:05.036
ADAM:  <i>For the record, Gina,</i>
<i>that's my mom's best friend.</i>

10:05.038 --> 10:06.137
Uh, can I go now?

10:06.139 --> 10:07.205
I've got a date
with Shirley Nagel.

10:07.207 --> 10:11.343
She's got 12 grandkids,
so you know she puts out.

10:11.345 --> 10:13.945
Cut the crap,
Albert, okay? Cut it!

10:13.947 --> 10:18.183
It's all life.
You lose your keys,
Barry gets some keys.

10:18.185 --> 10:19.684
It's the...
Circle of driving.

10:19.686 --> 10:23.822
Looks like I better
get on home
and take this all in.

10:23.824 --> 10:26.057
Can I have the keys?
No!

10:26.059 --> 10:27.392
You're out of my will!

10:27.394 --> 10:28.860
You're out of my will!

10:28.862 --> 10:31.196
That's right!
We'll see who croaks first!

10:31.198 --> 10:32.564
BARRY:
Wait. Wait, wait, wait.

10:32.566 --> 10:33.999
Does this mean I can drive?

10:34.001 --> 10:34.699
No!
Yes!

10:34.701 --> 10:38.970
Yeah, hon, I said Barry
was not ready, and you agreed.

10:38.972 --> 10:41.072
In my defense,
I wasn't listening.

10:41.074 --> 10:43.375
ADAM:  <i>Whenever my dad</i>
<i>disagreed with my mom,</i>

10:43.377 --> 10:45.010
<i>this would happen</i>
<i>five minutes later.</i>

10:45.012 --> 10:48.880
Who watches Adam sleep
in case his asthma kicks in?

10:48.882 --> 10:49.414
Me.

10:49.416 --> 10:50.515
ADAM:  <i>She'd guilt him</i>
<i>into submission.</i>

10:50.517 --> 10:55.286
Who bought the family
a new hamster because
you sat on Herbie?

10:55.288 --> 10:55.687
Me.

10:55.689 --> 10:56.921
ADAM:
<i>But not this time.</i>

10:56.923 --> 10:59.591
<i>See, my dad always had</i>
<i>a soft spot for Barry,</i>

10:59.593 --> 11:00.659
<i>so he decided</i>
<i>to help the kid.</i>

11:00.661 --> 11:03.228
I do all the dirty work
that you don't wanna do.

11:03.230 --> 11:05.897
Bevy, you live
for those things,

11:05.899 --> 11:07.599
and now that the kids
are growing older,

11:07.601 --> 11:09.768
your whole world
is falling apart.

11:09.770 --> 11:12.270
My world is fine,
thank you very much.

11:12.272 --> 11:12.837
Okay.

11:12.839 --> 11:14.572
If you got no problem
letting go,

11:14.574 --> 11:17.809
then I'm gonna take Barry
for a driving lesson.

11:17.811 --> 11:18.410
(SCOFFS)

11:18.412 --> 11:22.180
Ho-ho-ho! You two stuck
in the same car together?

11:22.182 --> 11:24.549
That'll go well.
Good luck not flipping out.

11:24.551 --> 11:28.053
I don't need luck.
I'm gonna teach him good.

11:28.055 --> 11:30.221
I'm gonna parent
the (BLEEP) out of him.

11:30.223 --> 11:33.825
Barry! Daddy's gonna
teach you how to drive!

11:33.827 --> 11:35.126
Seriously?

11:35.128 --> 11:37.062
Uh-huh!
Okay.

11:37.064 --> 11:39.631
(GRUNTING RHYTHMICALLY)

11:39.699 --> 11:42.367
<i>♪ Yeah, that's right,</i>
<i>Barry's drivin' ♪</i>

11:42.369 --> 11:44.602
Unreal. I raised a moron.

11:44.604 --> 11:46.404
(BELL DINGS)

11:46.406 --> 11:49.441
ADAM:  <i>My dad was determined</i>
<i>to do the impossible...</i>

11:49.443 --> 11:50.108
<i>Not yell.</i>

11:50.110 --> 11:52.944
Just stop screaming,
please!
Listen! Listen to me!

11:52.946 --> 11:53.712
Okay?
God!

11:53.714 --> 11:55.613
The brakes!
You're riding
the brake!

11:55.615 --> 11:57.916
You've gotta put your foot
on the gas sometime!

11:57.918 --> 11:59.451
You're going
so slow!
(HORN HONKS)

11:59.453 --> 12:00.351
Let him pass!
Who?

12:00.353 --> 12:02.520
The guy on the moped!
Let him pass!

12:02.522 --> 12:04.489
Go ahead!
Go ahead, okay.
Let him pass!

12:04.491 --> 12:05.323
(HORN HONKS)

12:05.325 --> 12:06.725
All right?
(MOPED MOTOR REVS)

12:06.727 --> 12:08.393
Now we're going
to make a right.

12:08.395 --> 12:12.363
Before we get to the right,
turn on your signal.

12:12.498 --> 12:13.732
(CLICK)

12:13.734 --> 12:14.299
Not the wiper.

12:14.301 --> 12:17.102
It's just smearing
everything around!
What is this?

12:17.104 --> 12:17.969
Come on.
Oh, my god.

12:17.971 --> 12:19.270
You gotta let me
out of this car, man.

12:19.272 --> 12:20.472
I can't die before
I cop a feel!

12:20.474 --> 12:23.641
Shut up, okay? You wanna die?
I'll kill you right now! Huh?

12:23.643 --> 12:25.376
Hey! I'll kill
both of you!

12:25.378 --> 12:28.546
Do not hit the child
in the back.

12:28.548 --> 12:29.914
That's way too advanced.

12:29.916 --> 12:30.482
Too advanced!

12:30.484 --> 12:33.685
Turn off the wipers.
Make a "U."
We're going home.

12:33.687 --> 12:34.652
Home? No, no!

12:34.654 --> 12:36.321
This is my one chance
to get my license,

12:36.323 --> 12:38.790
and I'm getting it,
all right?
You blew it!

12:38.792 --> 12:39.891
Stop the car!

12:39.893 --> 12:41.292
(BRAKES SQUEAL)

12:41.294 --> 12:42.894
(GEARS SHIFT)

12:43.229 --> 12:44.662
What are you doing?

12:44.664 --> 12:45.363
(HORN HONKS)

12:45.365 --> 12:48.666
Go around!
My son's a moron.

12:48.668 --> 12:51.202
Go around!
Just go! He's a moron!

12:51.204 --> 12:53.004
Get out.
I'm taking the wheel.
No!

12:53.006 --> 12:54.906
No. you said
it was my turn.

12:54.908 --> 12:56.341
Circle of driving.

12:56.343 --> 12:58.309
Open up!
Open up!
No! No!

12:58.311 --> 12:59.778
Open up!
No!

12:59.780 --> 13:03.014
No! No! No! No!

13:03.115 --> 13:06.117
Ah! You can't stay
in there forever.

13:06.786 --> 13:07.318
(HORNS HONKING)

13:07.320 --> 13:11.456
