<i>went from bad to worse.</i>

13:20.633 --> 13:22.767
<i>My mom arrived.</i>

13:24.103 --> 13:24.736
Who called her?

13:24.738 --> 13:27.572
ADAM:  <i>I'll give you a hint.</i>
<i>It was me.</i>

13:27.574 --> 13:29.374
Barry! Open up.

13:29.376 --> 13:33.511
Get out! Get out now!
Get out! Get out!

13:36.115 --> 13:37.615
Let me in!
Let me in!

13:37.617 --> 13:39.350
You're not gonna
get punished. Come on!

13:39.352 --> 13:40.151
We'll go for pizza!

13:40.153 --> 13:41.986
You wanna go for pizza?
Ice cream, too?

13:41.988 --> 13:43.454
Let me in!
Let me in!

13:43.456 --> 13:45.790
So this is what happens
when you're in charge, huh?

13:45.792 --> 13:48.726
(HORN HONKS,
MAN SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY)
City-wide traffic jam?

13:48.728 --> 13:50.762
Whose world
is falling apart now?

13:50.764 --> 13:51.596
MAN: Move the car!
Shut up!

13:51.598 --> 13:56.701
(EXHALES LOUDLY) Albert,
these kids adore you.

13:56.703 --> 13:58.169
Talk to the boy.

13:58.171 --> 13:59.771
Absolutely.

13:59.773 --> 14:02.373
Fight the power, Barry!
You can drive!

14:02.375 --> 14:03.675
It's a god-given right!

14:03.677 --> 14:05.443
ADAM:  <i>In that moment,</i>
<i>my dad expected my mom</i>

14:05.445 --> 14:08.880
<i>to go nuclear, but then</i>
<i>she did something even worse.</i>

14:08.882 --> 14:11.115
This is your mess.
You clean it up.

14:11.117 --> 14:14.853
ADAM:  <i>She left him</i>
<i>in charge of Barry.</i>

14:14.855 --> 14:19.924
I regret nothing!

14:26.732 --> 14:29.367
ADAM:  <i>In all the chaos,</i>
<i>Pops and I were able</i>
<i>to sneak out</i>

14:29.369 --> 14:32.303
<i>to work on</i>
<i>Operation Waffle Girl.</i>

14:32.305 --> 14:34.038
Welcome back, boys.
What'll it be?

14:34.040 --> 14:36.374
I don't know.
What do you think, Alan?

14:36.376 --> 14:40.144
Let's pull the trigger.
Two Monte Cristos,
all the trimmings.

14:40.146 --> 14:40.945
(CLEARS THROAT)

14:40.947 --> 14:42.046
All that fried
meat and cheese?

14:42.048 --> 14:45.183
Mom?
You're gonna be on
the bowl for hours.

14:45.185 --> 14:47.118
Mom! Leave now! Go!

14:47.120 --> 14:48.987
(NERVOUSLY)
I'll come back.

14:48.989 --> 14:51.489
(SINGSONGY)
Oh, I see what's going on.

14:51.491 --> 14:53.458
Someone has a crush.
(CHUCKLES)

14:53.460 --> 14:56.561
(NORMAL VOICE)
So adorable.
Not gonna happen.

14:56.563 --> 14:57.428
Excuse me?
Here we go.

14:57.430 --> 14:58.997
Well, I have to draw
the line somewhere.

14:58.999 --> 15:02.233
Erica's rushing off
to college,
Barry wants to drive,

15:02.235 --> 15:04.435
and now
you wanna date?

15:04.437 --> 15:06.738
You still play
with toy robots!

15:06.740 --> 15:07.872
They're GoBots!

15:07.874 --> 15:10.008
And one day,
they'll be worth millions.

15:10.010 --> 15:10.842
ADAM:  <i>They weren't.</i>

15:10.844 --> 15:13.144
Baby, you're
not ready for girls.

15:13.146 --> 15:15.213
You don't even
have pit hair.

15:15.215 --> 15:16.281
I have three.

15:16.283 --> 15:16.915
ADAM:  <i>I didn't.</i>

15:16.917 --> 15:17.949
Dad, how could you
encourage this?

15:17.951 --> 15:21.486
'Cause he's in sixth grade.
Loosen your damn grip, Bev.

15:21.488 --> 15:24.222
Yeah! I'm a man now!
A man with needs,

15:24.224 --> 15:27.125
and I need Zoe
and her sweet,
delicate boobs,

15:27.127 --> 15:29.627
and you can't stop me.

15:31.497 --> 15:33.097
(HUFFS)

15:36.435 --> 15:38.603
You're out of my will!

15:40.973 --> 15:43.207
Whatever that means!

15:44.009 --> 15:45.343
This is your fault,
you know.

15:45.345 --> 15:47.211
If I knew that's why
you drove him here,

15:47.213 --> 15:48.980
I never would've
allowed it.

15:48.982 --> 15:51.382
You wanna know why I won't
give up my license, Bev?

15:51.384 --> 15:55.386
You wanna get
with Shirley Nagel.
Yes, we get it.

15:55.388 --> 15:57.488
Shirley Nagel.
Are you kidding me?

15:57.490 --> 15:58.890
I got that locked down.

15:58.892 --> 16:00.224
But if you take away
my car,

16:00.226 --> 16:03.227
you take away my time
with my grandson.

16:03.229 --> 16:05.196
Getting waffles
with that little guy,

16:05.198 --> 16:07.899
it's the best part
of my week.

16:09.234 --> 16:10.802
Oh, dad.

16:11.437 --> 16:13.404
I didn't know that.

16:13.406 --> 16:17.208
You'll make it right, Bev.
I know you will.

16:20.512 --> 16:22.280
ADAM:  <i>As my mom realized</i>
<i>she had to let go,</i>

16:22.282 --> 16:26.551
<i>my dad decided it was time</i>
<i>to get more involved.</i>

16:26.719 --> 16:28.219
I guess you
were right, okay?

16:28.221 --> 16:30.555
Looks like
I'll never drive.

16:31.156 --> 16:34.392
Any dummy
can learn to drive,

16:34.394 --> 16:36.561
even a dummy like you.

16:36.563 --> 16:38.096
Come on, dad.

16:38.098 --> 16:40.098
You got me
an REO Speedwagon tape.

16:40.100 --> 16:42.066
You don't know
anything about me.

16:42.068 --> 16:43.668
Trust me. I do.

16:43.670 --> 16:47.739
I know you go through life
feeling all angry,

16:47.741 --> 16:50.375
let down, misunderstood.

16:50.776 --> 16:52.343
I get it.

16:52.345 --> 16:55.380
Wow. That's... Yeah.

16:55.382 --> 16:58.149
Do you ever cry
into your pillow?

16:58.151 --> 16:59.150
No, I don't cry
into my pillow.

16:59.152 --> 17:02.720
Who cries
in their pillow?
Not me. I don't.

17:03.689 --> 17:04.856
Here's what I'm gonna do.

17:04.858 --> 17:07.492
I'm gonna talk to your mom
and tell her

17:07.494 --> 17:10.028
that she's gotta let you
get your driver's license.

17:10.030 --> 17:10.895
Really?
Yes.

17:10.897 --> 17:13.965
Thank you, and can you also
convince her to get a hobby?

17:13.967 --> 17:15.900
Knitting, break dancing.
I know, I know.

17:15.902 --> 17:18.002
Anything besides us.
Yes.

17:18.004 --> 17:18.970
I'm working on it, kid.

17:18.972 --> 17:22.340
ADAM:  <i>Turns out</i>
<i>our dad did have</i>
<i>a good heart after all.</i>

17:22.342 --> 17:24.509
<i>He just had to open it up</i>
<i>once in a while.</i>

17:24.511 --> 17:28.446
You know what?
I don't say it a lot, but...

17:28.914 --> 17:31.916
You're not a total moron
all the time.

17:32.217 --> 17:34.018
(BELL DINGS)

17:34.186 --> 17:37.055
(HORN HONKS, ENGINE RUMBLES)

17:37.790 --> 17:38.990
Can I drive?

17:38.992 --> 17:40.358
(BRAKES SQUEAL)

17:40.360 --> 17:41.659
No!

17:43.829 --> 17:46.497
Oh, come on.
Not REO Speedwagon.
(TAPE PLAYER CLICKS)

17:46.499 --> 17:51.302
Seriously?
Hey, this is
good stuff, okay?

17:51.304 --> 17:53.104
I've been listening to it.

17:53.106 --> 17:53.704
(HUMMING ALONG)

17:53.706 --> 17:58.209
<i>♪ And yet I'm still afraid</i>
<i>to let it show</i>

17:58.744 --> 18:01.846
<i>♪ What started out</i>
<i>as friendship</i>

18:01.848 --> 18:04.182
<i>♪ Has grown stronger</i>

18:04.184 --> 18:04.649
Come on.

18:04.651 --> 18:09.520
<i>♪ ...had the strength</i>
<i>to let it show</i>

18:09.522 --> 18:10.988
Here we go! Join me.

18:10.990 --> 18:16.861
<i>♪ And I can't stop</i>
<i>this feeling anymore</i>

18:16.863 --> 18:17.962
<i>♪ I've forgotten</i>

18:17.964 --> 18:22.166
(BOTH)
<i>♪ What I started</i>
<i>fighting for</i>

18:22.168 --> 18:23.034
Look at you!

18:23.036 --> 18:27.505
<i>♪ It's time to bring</i>
<i>this ship into the shore</i>

18:27.507 --> 18:30.475
<i>♪ And throw away the oars</i>

18:30.477 --> 18:32.477
<i>♪ Forever</i>

18:34.813 --> 18:40.885
<i>♪ 'Cause I can't fight</i>
<i>this feeling anymore</i>

18:40.887 --> 18:46.357
<i>♪ I've forgotten</i>
<i>what I started fighting for ♪</i>

18:46.359 --> 18:48.993
What are you, uh, doing?

18:49.461 --> 18:51.229
Nothing.

18:51.964 --> 18:54.265
Those the kids'
baby blankets?

18:54.500 --> 18:56.134
You got me. I...

18:56.136 --> 18:57.869
Sometimes I smell 'em
when I feel sad.

18:57.871 --> 18:59.270
That's not weird, is it?

18:59.272 --> 19:01.739
Well, little weird.

19:06.211 --> 19:07.612
Yeah.

19:07.614 --> 19:08.446
My world is caving in.

19:08.448 --> 19:10.548
I mean, I've given
those kids everything,

19:10.550 --> 19:13.684
and now that, uh,
they're growing up

19:13.686 --> 19:17.555
and don't need me as much,
what do I have?

19:17.557 --> 19:20.591
Me. I'm not going anywhere.

19:23.629 --> 19:27.265
All right,
let me have a... A sniff.

19:30.903 --> 19:36.741
<i>♪ And I can't fight</i>
<i>this feeling anymore</i>

19:36.743 --> 19:43.047
<i>♪ I've forgotten what</i>
<i>I started fighting for</i>

19:43.049 --> 19:48.019
<i>♪ It's time to bring this ship</i>
<i>into the shore</i>

19:48.021 --> 19:54.258
<i>♪ And throw away</i>
<i>the oars forever</i>

19:54.760 --> 19:56.827
<i>♪ 'Cause I can't fight</i>
<i>this feeling... ♪</i>

19:56.829 --> 19:59.964
Forget about the diner.
They just opened this place.

19:59.966 --> 20:01.098
I think you may like it.

20:01.100 --> 20:07.271
<i>♪ I've forgotten what</i>
<i>I started fighting for</i>

20:07.273 --> 20:12.510
<i>♪ It's time to bring</i>
<i>this ship into the shore</i>

20:12.578 --> 20:18.449
<i>♪ And throw away</i>
<i>the oars forever</i>

20:19.117 --> 20:21.452
<i>♪ 'Cause I can't fight</i>
<i>this feeling anymore ♪</i>

20:21.454 --> 20:26.090
ADAM:  <i>And with that,</i>
<i>the circle of driving</i>
<i>was finally complete.</i>

20:26.092 --> 20:31.696
<i>♪ I've forgotten what</i>
<i>I started fighting for</i>

20:31.698 --> 20:35.866
<i>♪ And if I had to crawl</i>
<i>upon the floor</i>

20:35.868 --> 20:39.036
<i>♪ Come crashing</i>
<i>through your door ♪</i>

20:43.508 --> 20:45.109
(SIGHS)

20:45.477 --> 20:47.778
I raised a moron.

20:47.780 --> 20:49.513
